ructionism. Throughout the textbook, substantive themes are illustrated by boxed examples and case studies. The author focuses on principles and theory and their application in the process of constructing housing policy, ensuring that the book will be a vital resource for undergraduate and postgraduate level students of housing and planning and related social policy modules.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aHousing policyzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aLund, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311119663340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447330479423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447330479/original  a978-3-11-119663-3  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles